# Festag auth CTAs

## Light mode

Soft white CTAs (Weiter, SSO, Apple, Docs „Alle anzeigen“, Security CTA):

```css
background: #ffffff;
color: #1e1e20;
border: 1px solid rgba(30, 30, 32, 0.08); /* very light hairline */
box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04); /* soft shadow below only */
```

Hover: stay `#ffffff` + same hairline `rgba(30,30,32,0.08)` + soft lift `0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.06)`  
Active: `#f9f9fa` + same hairline + soft bottom `0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.04)` — **no inset top highlight**, **no louder stroke**

Auth light canvas is one continuous fill on `.al-root` (`#f7f8f8`). `.al-desktop-left` stays **transparent** — never its own white/gray panel that lifts off the page.

## Dark mode

Soft slate fill with a **minimal white hairline** (barely visible edge on OLED):

```css
background: rgba(186, 194, 210, 0.08);
color: rgba(245, 245, 247, 0.88);
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
```

Hover/active lift the fill and hairline slightly (`0.09` / `0.07`). Tokens: `--festag-btn-dark-border*`.

## Shared

CTA styles are hard-locked with `!important` on `.al-root … .al-btn…` so globals `button { border:none }` and `button:focus { box-shadow:none }` cannot flatten them.

Tokens live on `.al-root` as `--festag-btn-dark-*` so they never inherit portal dark html tokens (that made buttons invisible on white).

## Inputs

Sana-style outer hairline on auth email/fields in **both** themes. No focus rings / glow shadows. Focus changes **stroke only** — never a fill step. Focus stroke uses the Google CTA accent (`#5B647D` / `--al-accent`).

**Light:** transparent fill + dark ink idle stroke:

```css
background: transparent;
border: 1px solid rgba(30, 30, 32, 0.15); /* --festag-input-border */
/* hover / filled */
border-color: rgba(30, 30, 32, 0.20); /* --festag-input-border-hover */
/* focus */
border-color: #5B647D; /* --festag-input-border-focus — Google accent */
/* background stays transparent */
```

**Dark:** transparent fill + white idle stroke, same accent on focus:

```css
background: transparent;
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15); /* --festag-input-border */
/* hover / filled */
border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.20); /* --festag-input-border-hover */
/* focus */
border-color: #5B647D; /* --festag-input-border-focus — same as light */
```

Autofill may use a canvas-matched inset paint (`#f7f8f8` light / soft slate dark) but must keep the same outer stroke — never reintroduce gray field fills in light.

## Do not

- Dual/heavy marketing shadows
- Borderless white-on-white in light (need the soft hairline)
- Thick / opaque strokes in dark CTAs (keep ~6% white hairline only)
- Inset top strokes / `inset 0 1px …` on idle or hover
- Thicker “3D platform” bars (`0 1.5px 0`)
- Gray light-mode field fills (`#EEEEF0` / `#E4E4E9`) or fill-step on focus
- Reintroduce fill-only auth inputs without the outer stroke
